Apache Spark
What is Spark

Apache Spark is a fast distributed data processing engine designed for large-scale data analytics.

Unlike Hadoop MapReduce, Spark performs computations in memory, which makes it significantly faster.

Why Spark is Faster

Spark keeps data in memory instead of repeatedly writing to disk.

Performance comparison:

Framework	Processing
Hadoop MapReduce	Disk-based
Spark	In-memory

Spark can be 10–100x faster than MapReduce for many workloads.

Core Components of Spark

1. Spark Core

The main engine responsible for distributed task execution and memory management.

2. Spark SQL

Used for structured data processing and SQL queries.

Example:

SELECT count(*) FROM users;

3. Spark Streaming

Used for real-time data processing.

Example:

Live data from sensors

Social media streams

Financial transactions

4. MLlib

Spark's machine learning library.

Provides algorithms for:

classification

clustering

regression

recommendation systems

5. GraphX

Used for graph processing.

Example:

Social network analysis

Hadoop vs Spark
Feature	Hadoop	Spark
Processing type	Batch processing	Batch + Real-time
Speed	Slower	Much faster
Data storage	HDFS	Can use HDFS
Memory usage	Disk-based	In-memory
Complexity	More complex	Easier to program
Industry Trend

In modern data engineering pipelines:

Hadoop is mostly used for distributed storage (HDFS).

Spark is used for data processing and analytics.

Typical architecture:

Data Sources
      ↓
HDFS / Data Lake
      ↓
Spark Processing
      ↓
Analytics / Machine Learning
