Conclusion

Apache Hadoop and Apache Spark are fundamental technologies in the big data ecosystem.

Hadoop provides scalable distributed storage and batch processing, while Spark offers high-speed data processing with advanced analytics capabilities.

Together, they enable organizations to process and analyze massive datasets efficiently, making them essential tools for modern data engineering and analytics solutions.
